block.comment: This script fixes the position the stage sprites so that it makes it look like the dragon is moving -- depending on what stage sprite it is, we multiply by which stage sprite it is -- because this is the first one, we multiply by 0. If it was the second one, we multiply by 1, ect.
This whole script first starts out by making sure that the dragon doesn't go below the edge
This is adding jump functionality to our dragon
This if statement, along with all the other if statements restart the game

scripts.comment: This is for the dragon to keep scrolling to the right -- we defined a global variable "scrollx" which will allow us to scroll through the x-axis -- because we have pinned all the stage sprites to certain positions in the x-axis which are reflected in each stage sprite's scripts -- we implemented the same
This for when we initially set the dragon's position to the beginnning

block.comment: This script fixes the position the obstacle sprites -- the cacti -- so that it makes it look like the dragon is moving past the obstacles-- again we fix the "x" position to be what is written inside the forever loop, depending on which cacti you are on, you will want to multiply it by 2, then 3, then 4, to spread out obstacles
